                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2602.05327/x2.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2:The overall framework of ProAct which operates in two stages to internalize lookahead reasoning capabilities. Stage 1: Grounded Lookahead Distillation establishes the reasoning paradigm. It constructs high-quality lookahead search trees via environmental probing (MCTS) and distills these complex trajectories into compressed, explicit reasoning chains. Stage 2: Online Reinforcement Learning with Monte-Carlo Critic which refines the lookahead reasoning accuracy of agent using a Policy-Gradient framework (e.g., PPO or GRPO). We introduce a plug-and-play MC-Critic that provides low-variance value estimates by aggregating discounted returns fromMMparallel trajectories generated by a lightweight random policy.",
